A nationwide public holiday to remember, annually:-
 
• the bravery and dedication of NHS staff putting their own lives at risk to help us in a time of national crisis;

• the retirees who have returned to service in the country’s time of need;

• the sacrifices, whilst also commemorating and celebrating the memories, of those who have died whilst treating others.

Our NHS staff have treated others, knowing that the disease is highly contagious and has no cure. 

Heroes worthy of our thanks.
